Most of the country is expected to experience a sunny Monday, according to the South African Weather Service. The weather in your region It will be fine and cool in Gauteng. The expected UVB sunburn index will be high. Mpumalanga will be fine and cool to cold, but warm in the Lowveld where it will be partly cloudy. Morning mist is expected along the escarpment of  Limpopo where it will be cloudy at first. Otherwise fine and cool to warm but partly cloudy in the eastern and northern parts. It will be fine and cool in the North West. Free State will be fine and cool, but cold in the south and along the Lesotho border. It will be cool but cold over the southern interior in the Northern Cape. The wind along the coast will be moderate south-easterly becoming fresh in the afternoon. In the Western Cape it will be fine and cool, but partly cloudy and cold over the southwest and south coast and adjacent interior, with morning fog and evening light rain. The wind along the coast will be light and variable in the south at first, becoming moderate to fresh westerly, otherwise moderate southerly to south-westerly becoming fresh southerly to south-easterly in the evening. The expected UVB sunburn index will be low. The Eastern Cape is expected to be fine. Morning fog patches is places in the south and it will be cold in the north. The wind along the coast will be fresh westerly in the north at first, otherwise moderate north westerly, becoming fresh to strong south westerly from the south from late afternoon. There will be morning fog over the north western interior of KwaZulu-Natal. Otherwise, it will be fine and cool but warm in the north-east. The wind along the coast will be moderate southerly to south-westerly. The expected UVB sunburn index will be moderate.  Click here to see the specific forecast for your city over the next few days  